		</time>
		<geography>
			<locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction location="CN">
				<descriptionOfRestrictions xml:lang="en">This study performs a life-cycle assessment for a photovoltaic (PV) system with multi crystalline silicon (multi-Si) modules in China</descriptionOfRestrictions>
				<descriptionOfRestrictions xml:lang="zh">这项研究为中国的多晶硅组件光伏系统提供了生命週期评估</descriptionOfRestrictions>
			</locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction>
		</geography>
		<technology>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="en">Metallurgical silicon smelting described in this data set is utilized for the production of multi-crystalline silicon, which is an essential component in photovoltaic (PV) systems for solar energy capture and conversion. This process specifically refers to the carbon-thermal reduction method to produce silicon with a purity of 99%. The multi-crystalline silicon (or multi-Si) is subsequently used in the production of various photovoltaic components including wafers, ingots, cells, and modules for solar panel assembly.</technologicalApplicability>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="zh">本数据集描述的冶金硅熔炼过程用于生产多晶硅，这是太阳能光伏（PV）系统中捕获和转换太阳能必不可少的组成部分。该过程特指使用碳热还原法生产纯度为99%的硅。所生产的多晶硅（即多硅）随后用于生产包括晶圆、铸锭、电池和模块在内的各种光伏组件，用于组装太阳能面板。</technologicalApplicability>
			<referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture type="source data set" refObjectId="7506d463-2654-e8c5-5be0-f5ac10ac3546" uri="../sources/7506d463-2654-e8c5-5be0-f5ac10ac3546.xml">
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="en">GSvEbT284otn6Uxk366cUzLpnKe.png</common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture>
		</technology>
	</processInformation>
	<modellingAndValidation>
		<LCIMethodAndAllocation>
			<typeOfDataSet>Unit process, single operation</typeOfDataSet>
			<LCIMethodPrinciple>Attributional</LCIMethodPrinciple>
			<deviationsFromLCIMethodPrinciple xml:lang="en">None</deviationsFromLCIMethodPrinciple>
			<deviationsFromLCIMethodPrinciple xml:lang="zh">无</deviationsFromLCIMethodPrinciple>
			<LCIMethodApproach>Allocation</LCIMethodApproach>
			<deviationsFromLCIMethodApproaches xml:lang="en">The goal of this study was to quantitatively assess the life-cycle environmental impacts of PV systems in China and provide a scientific basis for policy-making regarding the sustainable development of Chinese PV industry.</deviationsFromLCIMethodApproaches>
			<deviationsFromLCIMethodApproaches xml:lang="zh">本研究旨在定量评估中国光伏系统的生命周期环境影响，为中国光伏产业的可持续发展提供科学依据</deviationsFromLCIMethodApproaches>
			<deviationsFromModellingConstants xml:lang="en">None</deviationsFromModellingConstants>
			<deviationsFromModellingConstants xml:lang="zh">无</deviationsFromModellingConstants>
		</LCIMethodAndAllocation>
		<dataSourcesTreatmentAndRepresentativeness>
			<deviationsFromCutOffAndCompletenessPrinciples xml:lang="en">None</deviationsFromCutOffAndCompletenessPrinciples>
			<deviationsFromCutOffAndCompletenessPrinciples xml:lang="zh">无</deviationsFromCutOffAndCompletenessPrinciples>
			<dataSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples xml:lang="en">The inventory data, including the material consumption andenvironmental emissions involved in the production of solar-grade silicon, wafers, ingots, cells, and modules, were mainly collected from companies that represent the current domain multi-Si PV technologies in China. The energy consumption data referred to the report “Clean Production ofSolar PV in China” (Li and Chang, 2012). The data of MG-Si production was from literature about MG-Si produced in China</dataSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples>
			<dataSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples xml:lang="zh">库存数据，包括太阳能级硅、晶圆、铸锭、电池和模块生产所涉及的材料消耗和环境排放，主要来自代表中国当前领域多硅光伏技术的公司。能源消费数据参考了“中国太阳能光伏的清洁生产”报告(Li and Chang，2012)。多晶硅生产数据来源于国内有关的文献资料</dataSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples>
			<deviationsFromSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples xml:lang="en">None</deviationsFromSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples>
			<deviationsFromSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples xml:lang="zh">无</deviationsFromSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples>
			<deviationsFromTreatmentAndExtrapolationPrinciples xml:lang="en">None</deviationsFromTreatmentAndExtrapolationPrinciples>
			<deviationsFromTreatmentAndExtrapolationPrinciples xml:lang="zh">无</deviationsFromTreatmentAndExtrapolationPrinciples>
			<referenceToDataSource type="source data set" refObjectId="e5f8a793-a35e-41c2-aad3-12c44660d71b" uri="../sources/e5f8a793-a35e-41c2-aad3-12c44660d71b.xml">
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="en"> Fu, Y., Liu, X. &amp; Yuan, Z. Life-cycle assessment of multi-crystalline photovoltaic (PV) systems in China. Journal of Cleaner Production 86, 180–190 (2015).</common:shortDescription>
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="zh"> Fu, Y., Liu, X. &amp; Yuan, Z. Life-cycle assessment of multi-crystalline photovoltaic (PV) systems in China. Journal of Cleaner Production 86, 180–190 (2015).</common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToDataSource>
			<useAdviceForDataSet xml:lang="en">When using this data set, users should consider the methodological framework provided by the Life Cycle Assessment (LCA) of a PV system with multi-crystalline silicon modules in China. Users should ensure to reference the appropriate scope of the study, which focuses on material consumption, environmental emissions, and energy usage from the Chinese PV industry perspective. When applicable, users must also take into account the technological applicability of the data, particularly when projecting the LCA study results for policy making or in different geographical contexts. Recycling and end-of-life considerations should also be included where relevant.</useAdviceForDataSet>
			<useAdviceForDataSet xml:lang="zh">使用此数据集时，用户应考虑由中国多晶硅组件光伏系统的生命周期评估（LCA）提供的方法论框架。用户应确保引用研究的适当范围，该研究侧重于从中国光伏产业的角度考量的材料消耗、环境排放和能源使用。在适用的情况下，用户还必须考虑数据的技术适用性，特别是在预测LCA研究结果以供政策制定或在不同地理环境中应用时。还应在相关的地方包括回收和产品寿命终结的考量。</useAdviceForDataSet>
		</dataSourcesTreatmentAndRepresentativeness>
